<doc id="485119" wikidata="Q808631" url="?curid=485119" title="Baron Inchyra">
<text>Baron Inchyra, of St Madoes in the County of Perth, is a title in the Peerage of the United Kingdom. It was created on 2 February 1962 for the diplomat Sir Frederick Millar, who had previously served as British Ambassador to West Germany. , the title is held by his grandson, the third Baron, who succeeded in 2011.

The family seat is Inchyra House, near Glencarse, Perth.

==Barons Inchyra (1962)==
*Frederick Robert Hoyer Millar, 1st Baron Inchyra (1900–1989)
*Robert Charles Reneke Hoyer Millar, 2nd Baron Inchyra (1935–2011)
*(Christian) James Charles Hoyer Millar, 3rd Baron Inchyra (b. 1962)

The heir apparent is the present holder&#x27;s only son, Hon. Jake Christian Robert Hoyer Millar (b. 1996).

