<doc id="485157" wikidata="Q56679091" url="?curid=485157" title="Pokhara Premier League">
<text>Pokhara Premier League () was a franchise Twenty20 cricket tournament held in Nepal. Also known as by PPL. The tournament was managed by the Queen&#x27;s Event Management. It was an auction-based tournament.

== History ==
Led by the board member of Cricket Association of Nepal (CAN) Chhumbi Lama, the idea of organizing it in Pokhara was mainly to establish it as one of the cricketing hubs within the country.

